article.headline: S. Dakota 77, Chicago St. 73
article.story: CHICAGO -- Tyler Cain's double-double helped South Dakota defeat Chicago State 77-73 on Saturday. Cain had 19 points and 13 rebounds for the Coyotes (17-9, 8-1 Great West Conference), who won their eighth in a row. Cain became the second player in South Dakota history with more than 1,000 rebounds. He has 1,013. Roman Gentry scored a team-high 20 points, with Mitchell Bouie adding 16 and Jake Thomas 14. Christian Wall led the Cougars (8-21, 3-8) with 20 points. Carl Montgomery added 17, Antonio Lofton 15 and Kabangu Kasamba 11. The Coyotes led by double digits in the second half, but the Cougars clawed within 75-73 with 41 seconds left after a 10-1 run. South Dakota ran the clock down to 5 seconds, then missed a shot. But Cain grabbed the offensive rebound, and Thomas hit two free throws to seal it.
